</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">NS</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">49 (55)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">33 (29)</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">AHS</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">78 (67)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">71 (69)</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">TAHS</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">33 (55)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">28 (41)</td></tr></tbody></table></alternatives><table-wrap-foot><fn id="t002fn001"><p>Shock30&#x02019;: end of controlled bleeding before beginning of infusion; Obs30&#x02019;: 30 minutes after the end of infusion. Obs60&#x02019;: 60 minutes after the end of infusion. NS: Normal saline; AHS: Albumin plus hypertonic saline; TAHS: Terlipressin plus albumin hypertonic saline. CI: Cardiac index; SVI: Stroke volume index; GEDVI: Global end diastolic index; PPV: Pulse pressure variation; bTOI: Brain tissue oxygenation index; PgCO<sub>2</sub>: Gastric intramucosal pCO<sub>2</sub>; ScvO<sub>2</sub>: Central venous blood oxygen saturation. &#x00394;% (SD): variation (in percentage) respect to the previous moment.</p></fn><fn id="t002fn002"><p>
